  "root_text": {
    "iti9:0.1": "Itivuttaka 9 ",
    "iti9:0.2": "Ekakanipāta ",
    "iti9:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti9:0.4": "Lobhapariññāsutta ",
    "iti9:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti9:2.1": "“Lobhaṁ, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṁ aparijānaṁ tattha cittaṁ avirājayaṁ appajahaṁ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya. ",
    "iti9:2.2": "Lobhañca kho, bhikkhave, abhijānaṁ parijānaṁ tattha cittaṁ virājayaṁ pajahaṁ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāyā”ti. ",
    "iti9:2.3": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti9:2.4": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti9:3.1": "“Yena lobhena luddhāse, ",
    "iti9:3.2": "sattā gacchanti duggatiṁ; ",
    "iti9:3.3": "Taṁ lobhaṁ sammadaññāya, ",
    "iti9:3.4": "pajahanti vipassino; ",
    "iti9:3.5": "Pahāya na punāyanti, ",
    "iti9:3.6": "imaṁ lokaṁ kudācanan”ti. ",
    "iti9:4.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti9:4.2": "Navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti9:0.1": "So It Was Said 9 ",
    "iti9:0.2": "The Book of the Ones ",
    "iti9:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti9:0.4": "Complete Understanding of Greed ",
    "iti9:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti9:2.1": "“Mendicants, without directly knowing and completely understanding greed, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering. ",
    "iti9:2.2": "By directly knowing and completely understanding greed, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.” ",
    "iti9:2.3": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti9:2.4": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti9:3.1": "“When overcome by greed ",
    "iti9:3.2": "beings go to a bad place. ",
    "iti9:3.3": "Having rightly understood that greed, ",
    "iti9:3.4": "the discerning give it up. ",
    "iti9:3.5": "Once they’ve given it up, ",
    "iti9:3.6": "they never return to this world.” ",
    "iti9:4.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
